description.p:
With reference to FIGS. 3, 4a, 4b and 4c, the feeding device is formed by:



    

a) a main metal roller R1, directly connected to a first brushless motor M1, that has the functions of feeding and the control of the speed of advancement of the band;

b) a pressure roller R2 covered with an elastic material (rubber) and which is also connected to a second brushless motor M2, with the function of free speed of rotation and variable torque, that adapts its rotation on the basis of as much as is permitted by the band itself, generating the running of the longer upper band, keeping it parallel to the lower base band.
